      <h2>Features Worth Paying For</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Rechargeable batteries:</strong> USB-C charging means one less battery type to stock. The Kiprim and Tadeto models both use USB-C.</li>
        <li><strong>Magnetic mount:</strong> Being able to stick your laser to a metal stud or door frame for hands-free measuring is a game-changer. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FNMBFFP7?tag=sciencesolved-20">262ft Laser with Digital Angle Finder</a> includes both magnetic mounting and an angle finder.</li>
        <li><strong>Backlit display:</strong> Essential for dim job sites and bright outdoor conditions. Most models over $50 include this.</li>
        <li><strong>IP rating:</strong> Dust and water resistance matter on construction sites. Look for IP54 or higher if you work in rough conditions.</li>
        <li><strong>Carrying case:</strong> A good case protects your investment. BOSCH models typically include a pouch or hard case.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What to Avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Ultra-cheap no-name lasers ($15–25):</strong> They're inaccurate, fragile, and die after a few weeks. You'll spend more replacing them than buying a quality unit once.</li>
        <li><strong>Over-buying on range:</strong> If you primarily work indoors, 300+ ft is overkill. You're paying for specs you'll never use.</li>
        <li><strong>Ignoring the laser class:</strong> Class 2 lasers are safe for general use. Class 3R requires eye protection. Stick with Class 2 for most construction work.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
      <p>For the vast majority of contractors, the sweet spot is a 165 ft range, ±1/16" accuracy, and a reputable brand. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B076C3TB8P?tag=sciencesolved-20">BOSCH GLM165-40 Blaze Pro</a> is the industry gold standard for a reason — it balances range, accuracy, durability, and price better than anything else on the market.</p>
      <p>If you work outdoors or need extreme range, step up to the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DF7PB4QP?tag=sciencesolved-20">Tadeto Dual Laser 393FT</a>. If you need Bluetooth for data transfer, the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B015FCJTEA?tag=sciencesolved-20">BOSCH GLM 50 C</a> is your best bet. And if you're on a tight budget, the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C76CPGC7?tag=sciencesolved-20">BOSCH GLM100-23</a> gets you 80% of the capability for half the price.</p>
